⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Three Antichrists
node N1 · N1 · ⟦The Three Antichrists:N1:88ea58⟧

WHO   — The Three Antichrists — the three tyrants of the reading
WHAT  — The reception-myth of the "three antichrists" — a retrofitted scheme assembled by later commentators from scattered, cryptic quatrains, presented as if it were the prophet's own design.
WHERE — N1 · Nostradamus  Framework inputs: Les Propheties (1555)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a corpus vague enough invites a pattern; because each terrible age looks back into the verse and finds its own monster waiting there; because two confirmed tyrants make the unnamed third feel inevitable.
HOW   — By plucking obscure words — "PAU NAY LORON" read as an anagram for Napoleon, "Hister" read as Hitler though it names the Danube — and binding them into a sequence the text never states.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Two tyrants the readers found, and a third they are still waiting for — but the prophet never wrote the number three.

